# TypeScript standards — backend

- Prefer explicit return types on public service methods.
- Never use `any` to silence errors — narrow with typed exceptions or
  guards instead.
- Env access goes through `@nestjs/config` + the zod schema in
  `src/config/env.validation.ts` — do not read `process.env` ad hoc in
  feature services (except e2e bootstrap).
- Keep Nest's `nodenext` module settings; do not reintroduce deprecated
  `baseUrl` without a `paths` migration (TS 6+).
- Fail closed on bad input (HTTP 400 via ValidationPipe) rather than
  coercing silently when it would change domain meaning.
